Leaves l/w = 2/3 , 1-2-pinnately or -palmately lobed ; often 2-, 3-, or 5-ribbed;
Glands (1-) 2-5 (-10+), lateral, two on each side of lateral stamen, median glands absent;
Flowers between 1.0 and 2.0 cm long; few to many; brownish red to bright orange;
Stems to 5 m., narrow to broad, weakly to strongly hairy, more than 3, at most 8.
Stems len-gths unknown.
Leaves (cau-line);
